_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     This function reads either a single shapefile or multiple
     shapefiles.  For  multiple shapefiles, all of the shapefiles must
     be the same type, i.e.,  point, polyline, or polygon.

_U_s_a_g_e:

     read.shape(filename=NULL)

_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

filename: name of the shapefile without any extension.  If filename 
          equals a shapefile name, than that shapefile is read.  If
          filename  equals NULL, then all of the shapefiles in the
          current directory are  read.  The default is NULL.

_V_a_l_u_e:

     An sp package object containing information in the shapefile.  The
     object is assigned class "SpatialPointsDataFrame",
     "SpatialLinesDataFrame", or "SpatialPolygonsDataFrame"
     corresponding to the shapefile type, i.e., point, polyline, or
     polygon, respectively.  For further information regarding the
     output object, see documentation for the sp package.

